ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIB.name: ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIB

revisions.description: Added 2 objects to cwacsExtStatsTable (extension of cwacsTable): cwacsTotalCR, cwacsAisSuppressCount.
Added 3 more objects to cwacsExtStatsTable (extension of cwacsTable): cwacsUsedConns, cwacsUtilizedCR, cwacsUsedVadConns.
Indentation/Editorial changes made across the MIB.

1. Added Following objects to cwacsTable, as upper 32-bits for 64-bit wide counters: cwacsHighIngRcvCLP0, cwacsHighIngRcvCLP1, cwacsHighIngXmtCLP0, cwacsHighIngXmtCLP1, cwacsHighIngCLP0CoSDiscard, cwacsHighIngCLP1CoSDiscard, cwacsHighIngCLP0UpcDiscard, cwacsHighIngCLP1UpcDiscard, cwacsHighIngCLP0UpcTagged, cwacsHighIngRcvEFCI0, cwacsHighIngRcvEFCI1, cwacsHighIngEFCI0Discard, cwacsHighIngEFCI1Discard, cwacsHighIngRcvEOF1, cwacsHighIngEOF1Discard, cwacsHighEgrRcvCLP0, cwacsHighEgrRcvCLP1, cwacsHighEgrXmtCLP0, cwacsHighEgrXmtCLP1, cwacsHighEgrCLP0CoSDiscard, cwacsHighEgrCLP1CoSDiscard, cwacsHighEgrRcvEFCI0, cwacsHighEgrRcvEFCI1, cwacsHighEgrEFCI0Discard, cwacsHighEgrEFCI1Discard, cwacsHighEgrRcvEOF1, cwacsHighEgrEOF1Discard. 2. Added cwacsXTable which contains 64-bits wide counters.
1. Added cwaConnStatsTable for real time statistical counter objects. This table applies to only atm service module such as BXM.
1. Added cwacsStatsClear object to cwacsEntry to clear channel connection statistic counters.
Initial version of the MIB module.

ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIB.description: This module contains ATM switch connection related real time statistical counter objects.

cwacsTable.name: cwacsTable
cwacsTable.description: Contains traffic statistic information for every Channel entry in the atmTable. It is used to monitor the usage of the Channel in terms of Ingress(incoming direction) cells and Egress (outgoing direction) cells. In each direction counters are collected before and after the traffic management entity.

cwacsEntry.name: cwacsEntry
cwacsEntry.description: An entry in the ATM connection Channel statistic table. An entry is created for every Channel.

cwacsIngRcvCLP0.name: cwacsIngRcvCLP0
cwacsIngRcvCLP0.description: The number of valid CLP=0 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel prior to the traffic management entity.

cwacsIngRcvCLP1.name: cwacsIngRcvCLP1
cwacsIngRcvCLP1.description: The number of valid CLP=1 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel prior to the traffic management entity.

cwacsIngXmtCLP0.name: cwacsIngXmtCLP0
cwacsIngXmtCLP0.description: The number of valid CLP=0 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel after the traffic management entity.

cwacsIngXmtCLP1.name: cwacsIngXmtCLP1
cwacsIngXmtCLP1.description: The number of valid CLP=1 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel after the traffic management entity.

cwacsIngCLP0CoSDiscard.name: cwacsIngCLP0CoSDiscard
cwacsIngCLP0CoSDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwacsIngCLP1CoSDiscard.name: cwacsIngCLP1CoSDiscard
cwacsIngCLP1CoSDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=1 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwacsIngCLP0UpcDiscard.name: cwacsIngCLP0UpcDiscard
cwacsIngCLP0UpcDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the traffic policing entity due to UPC/PCR parameter violation. UPC(Usage Parameter Control) operation checks the validity of the user traffic on a connection. If incoming cells violate established user-network contract .If cell violates PCR(Peak Cell Rate) parameter for the connection it is discarded. Or else the cell is marked low priority by setting CLP=1.

cwacsIngCLP1UpcDiscard.name: cwacsIngCLP1UpcDiscard
cwacsIngCLP1UpcDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=1 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the traffic policing entity due to UPC/PCR parameter violation.

cwacsIngCLP0UpcTagged.name: cwacsIngCLP0UpcTagged
cwacsIngCLP0UpcTagged.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are tagged as low priority by UPC.

cwacsIngRcvEFCI0.name: cwacsIngRcvEFCI0
cwacsIngRcvEFCI0.description: The number of valid EFCI=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel before class of service queue. EFCI(Explicit Forward Congestion Indication) is an ATM header bit.

cwacsIngRcvEFCI1.name: cwacsIngRcvEFCI1

cwacsIngEFCI0Discard.name: cwacsIngEFCI0Discard
cwacsIngEFCI0Discard.description: The number of valid UPC/PCR parameter compliant EFCI=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue.

cwacsIngEFCI1Discard.name: cwacsIngEFCI1Discard
cwacsIngEFCI1Discard.description: The number of valid UPC/PCR parameter compliant EFCI=1 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue.

cwacsIngRcvOAM.name: cwacsIngRcvOAM

cwacsIngOAMDiscard.name: cwacsIngOAMDiscard

cwacsIngACR.name: cwacsIngACR
cwacsIngACR.description: Current value of the ingress ACR(Allowed Cell Rate) parameter. It is an ABR service parameter and is the current rate in cells/sec at which a source is allowed to send packets. For traffic type other than ABR this parameter is not instantiated. This variable is used for shaping the traffic going onto the backplane.

cwacsHCIngEFCI1Discard.description: The number of valid UPC/PCR parameter compliant EFCI=1 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCIngRcvEOF1.name: cwacsHCIngRcvEOF1
cwacsHCIngRcvEOF1.description: The number of valid EOF=1 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel PRIOR to the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCIngEOF1Discard.name: cwacsHCIngEOF1Discard
cwacsHCIngEOF1Discard.description: The number of valid EOF=1 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel which are discard at the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP0.name: cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP0
cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP0.description: The number of valid CLP=0 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel PRIOR to the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP1.name: cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP1
cwacsHCEgrRcvCLP1.description: The number of valid CLP=1 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel PRIOR to the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP0.name: cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP0
cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP0.description: The number of valid CLP=0 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel AFTER the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP1.name: cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP1
cwacsHCEgrXmtCLP1.description: The number of valid CLP=1 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel AFTER the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrCLP0CoSDiscard.name: cwacsHCEgrCLP0CoSDiscard
cwacsHCEgrCLP0CoSDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue due to overflow. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrCLP1CoSDiscard.name: cwacsHCEgrCLP1CoSDiscard
cwacsHCEgrCLP1CoSDiscard.description: The number of valid CLP=1 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue due to overflow. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI0.name: cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI0
cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI0.description: The number of valid EFCI=0 cells in the egress direction of this Channel before CoS queue. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI1.name: cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI1
cwacsHCEgrRcvEFCI1.description: The number of valid EFCI=1 cells in the egress direction of this Channel before the class of service queue. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrEFCI0Discard.name: cwacsHCEgrEFCI0Discard
cwacsHCEgrEFCI0Discard.description: The number of valid EFCI=0 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrEFCI1Discard.name: cwacsHCEgrEFCI1Discard
cwacsHCEgrEFCI1Discard.description: The number of valid EFCI=1 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the CoS queue. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrRcvEOF1.name: cwacsHCEgrRcvEOF1
cwacsHCEgrRcvEOF1.description: The number of valid EOF=1 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel PRIOR to the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwacsHCEgrEOF1Discard.name: cwacsHCEgrEOF1Discard
cwacsHCEgrEOF1Discard.description: The number of valid EOF=1 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel which are discarded at the traffic management entity. This counter carries 64-bit value of this statistic.

cwaConnStatsTable.name: cwaConnStatsTable
cwaConnStatsTable.description: Contains traffic statistic information for every Channel entry in the atmTable. It is used to monitor the usage of the Channel in terms of Ingress(incoming direction) cells and Egress (outgoing direction) cells. In each direction counters are collected before and after the traffic management entity. This table only applies to ATM service module such as BXM.

cwaConnStatsEntry.name: cwaConnStatsEntry
cwaConnStatsEntry.description: An entry in the ATM connection Channel statistic table. An entry is created for every Channel. These counters applies to Channels on ATM service module such as BXM.

cwaConnStatsIngRcv.name: cwaConnStatsIngRcv
cwaConnStatsIngRcv.description: The number of valid CLP=0 and CLP=1 ATM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel prior to the traffic management entity.

cwaConnStatsIngCLP0Discard.name: cwaConnStatsIngCLP0Discard
cwaConnStatsIngCLP0Discard.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the traffic policing entity due to UPC parameter violation and at the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwaConnStatsIngCLP1Discard.name: cwaConnStatsIngCLP1Discard
cwaConnStatsIngCLP1Discard.description: The number of valid CLP=1 cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the traffic policing entity due to UPC parameter violation and at the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwaConnStatsIngTotalDiscard.name: cwaConnStatsIngTotalDiscard
cwaConnStatsIngTotalDiscard.description: Total number of CLP=0 cells, CLP=1 cells, OAM cells, and RM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel that are discarded due to UPC parameter violation and the class of service queue overflow.

cwaConnStatsEgrXmt.name: cwaConnStatsEgrXmt
cwaConnStatsEgrXmt.description: The number of valid CLP=0 and CLP=1 ATM cells in the egress direction of this Channel prior to the traffic management entity.

cwaConnStatsEgrCLP0Discard.name: cwaConnStatsEgrCLP0Discard
cwaConnStatsEgrCLP0Discard.description: The number of valid CLP=0 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwaConnStatsEgrCLP1Discard.name: cwaConnStatsEgrCLP1Discard
cwaConnStatsEgrCLP1Discard.description: The number of valid CLP=1 cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded at the the class of service queue due to overflow.

cwaConnStatsEgrTotalDiscard.name: cwaConnStatsEgrTotalDiscard
cwaConnStatsEgrTotalDiscard.description: Total number of CLP=0 cells, CLP=1 cells, OAM cells, and RM cells in the egress direction of this Channel that are discarded due to the class of service queue overflow.

cwaConnStatsClear.name: cwaConnStatsClear
cwaConnStatsClear.description: The agent clears the channel statistics collection if it receives a set to value of true(1) request from a manager. Setting a value of false(2) has no implication.

cwacsExtStatsTable.name: cwacsExtStatsTable
cwacsExtStatsTable.description: This table is extension of cwacsTable and is used to store traffic statistic information for each channel. The information in this table is related to voice over aal2(VoAtm).

cwacsEgrAal2HecErrors.name: cwacsEgrAal2HecErrors
cwacsEgrAal2HecErrors.description: The number of egress AAL2 CPS(Common Part Sub-layer) PDUs dropped due to HEC (Header Error Control) error.

cwacsEgrAal2InvalidOsfCells.name: cwacsEgrAal2InvalidOsfCells
cwacsEgrAal2InvalidOsfCells.description: The Number of AAL2 cells dropped due to invalid OSF (OffSet Field) in the egress direction.

cwacsEgrAal2InvalidParCells.name: cwacsEgrAal2InvalidParCells
cwacsEgrAal2InvalidParCells.description: The Number of AAL2 cells dropped due to invalid Parity bit field in the egress direction.

cwacsAal2CpsSentPkts.name: cwacsAal2CpsSentPkts
cwacsAal2CpsSentPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets sent to the network.

cwacsAal2CpsRcvdPkts.name: cwacsAal2CpsRcvdPkts
cwacsAal2CpsRcvdPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets received from the network. This does not include the packets which are counted as error packets.

cwacsEgrAal2CpsInvalidCidPkts.name: cwacsEgrAal2CpsInvalidCidPkts
cwacsEgrAal2CpsInvalidCidPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets dropped in the egress direction due to invalid CID. The CID may be considered as invalid if - a) It is out of range. b) It is not configured CID is Channel ID of a voice channel which set-up within PVC/SVC(only AAL2) and the CID is unique within the context of PVC/SVC.

cwacsCacPassedCalls.name: cwacsCacPassedCalls
cwacsCacPassedCalls.description: The number of calls that passed successfully the CAC function. For example, CAC functionality is applied either due to: 1) The CRCX message sent to Voice Gateway from the Call Agent to set up a new connection OR AAL2 trunking application. or 2) Upspeed request due to Fax/modem tone detection on a connection configured for compression. For the initial version of Alabama release, only case 2 is valid.

cwacsCacRejectedCalls.name: cwacsCacRejectedCalls
cwacsCacRejectedCalls.description: The number of calls that got rejected due to CAC function. The CAC rejection was due to the bandwidth not being available on a given ATM connection.

cwacsIngXmtOAM.name: cwacsIngXmtOAM
cwacsIngXmtOAM.description: The number of valid OAM cells in the ingress direction of this Channel after the traffic management entity.

cwacsUsedConns.name: cwacsUsedConns
cwacsUsedConns.description: This attribute indicates the number of connections currently in used.

cwacsUtilizedCR.name: cwacsUtilizedCR
cwacsUtilizedCR.description: This attribute indicates the current utilized CR (cell Rate) applied for PVC connection.

cwacsUsedVadConns.name: cwacsUsedVadConns
cwacsUsedVadConns.description: This attribute indicates the number of connections currently using VAD (Voice Activity Detection).

cwacsTotalCR.name: cwacsTotalCR
cwacsTotalCR.description: This attribute indicates the Total CR (cell Rate) applied for PVC connection.

cwacsAisSuppressCount.name: cwacsAisSuppressCount
cwacsAisSuppressCount.description: This object holds the number of times that ATM network alarms were successfully suppressed and prevented from propagating onto the TDM side for this PVC.

cwacsBearerPVCTable.name: cwacsBearerPVCTable
cwacsBearerPVCTable.description: This table stores the bearer PVC statistic information.

cwacsBearerPVCEntry.name: cwacsBearerPVCEntry
cwacsBearerPVCEntry.description: Each entry represents a valid bearer PVC. An entry is added/deleted automatically when a bearer PVC is added/deleted. A bearer PVC excludes the secondary one in a dual PVC pair.

cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMin.name: cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMin
cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMin.description: The minimum available bandwidth of a bearer PVC in the statistics interval.

cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMax.name: cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMax
cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWMax.description: The maximum available bandwidth of a bearer PVC in the statistics interval.

cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWAvg.name: cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWAvg
cwacsAvailableBearerPVCBWAvg.description: The average available bandwidth of a bearer PVC in the statistics interval.

cwacsBearerPVCSinceLastReset.name: cwacsBearerPVCSinceLastReset
cwacsBearerPVCSinceLastReset.description: The elapsed time (in seconds) since the last periodic reset.

ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Cisco statistics MIB.

ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIBCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for the Cisco statistics MIB.

ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIBCompliance5.description: The compliance statement for the Cisco statistics MIB.

ciscoWanAtmConnStatMIBCompliance6.description: The compliance statement for the Cisco statistics MIB.
